[02/03/2025, 20:18:18] Esme: Ladies and germs‚Ä¶
I present to you:

*The hairbrush incident*
Picture this‚Ä¶
I‚Äôm laying in my bed, as any adolescent does on a Sunday night, watching a tv show while contemplating my existence as the crushing realisation that I have school in the morning bears down on my tired shoulders.

Subconsciously, I reach over to my bedside table and grab hold of a rounded hairbrush. I start to brush through my luscious locks, feeling the silky smooth strands of hair as they run through the plastic bristles. All of a sudden, it was like a lightbulb went off above my head. It‚Äôs light so strong and appealing that I could not ignore the illumination and its call. 

I brush a large strand of hair, at the very front of my head, down to the ends. Promptly, I roll it up to my head as one would do with hair rollers. 
‚ÄòThis is fine.‚Äô I think, under the foolish assumption that I would simply be able to roll the brush back the way it came. 

My fingers grasp the handle of the brush with perseverance and prepare to smoothly remove the brush from my hair. I pull and‚Ä¶

*juck* ‚Ä¶ *juck*

My hair is stuck in the fucking brush. 
THE BRUSH IS STUCK TO MY HEAD 

I rush to the bathroom and desperately try to pull it out; the however; the brush holds no mercy and my pleas remain unheard. After roughly ten minutes of this pain and suffering I stick my head under the bath tap and cover my head in conditioner, thinking this would aid to relieve the tension and tangles on my head. 
It did not.

I am free.
